The Clover Club dates back to pre-prohibition Philadelphia, when it was created in the gentleman’s club at the Bellevue-Stratford hotel. You could replace the egg white for an equal quantity of pineapple juice; in which, case omit the cane sugar. It’s a simple classic that’s just the thing to celebrate Independence Day. Serves 1 3 raspberries50ml gin – we use Tanqueray No Ten15ml fresh lemon juice10ml cane syrup1 egg white (or pineapple juice - see introduction) Muddle the raspberries in the base of a shaker or toby tin, then add all the ingredients and dry shake to set the egg white. Add ice, shake again and serve. • Harry Ballmann, head of drinks, Folie, London W1